      "comment": "COMPTON SHELLY (1) comes here after a sizzling OPEN win at Mt Gambier over 400m in 22.85. In winning form and can measure up again. PADUCAH (8) stalked the lead and fought on well to finish a neck away in third (22.59) at this track in a Grade 6 over 395m. Has a strong record from this draw, notching two wins and five minor placings from seven starts. Expected to feature. SEBON BOLT (2) finished fourth last time but the start prior broke the clock when winning over 400m at Gawler, taking a Other in a handy 22.77. Top win two back and can measure up again. TOORA GRACIE (4) looks an each-way chance.",
